  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Minimizing the Spread of COVID 19 through Inter-faith Based Response in West Guji, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the project is 1, Reduction and mitigation of potential impact of COVID 19 pandemic on health systems, social services and economic activity 2) strengthening and raising awareness level of communities to bring recommended behavioural changes, such as social distancing, handwashing and sanitation. 3) Advocate for the poor and marginalized communities who are affected most during natural and human induced disasters and the pandemic.
&#x2022; Awareness raising and public Education. 
&#x2022; Establishing hand washing 
&#x2022; Providing support to health facilities and health workers:
&#x2022; Empowering faith actors, traditional leaders and local actors:
&#x2022; Capacity building training:
&#x2022; Awareness raising on COVID with in faith community:
 &#x2022; Conduct a study on the role of faith leaders to fight COVID 19:
&#x2022; Organize Learning and Advocacy plat form with FBO and faith leaders:</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Up on the completion of the  project, there will be: increased knowledge on COVID 19, mitigation of any adverse impacts of the outbreak improved in areas like financial situation for the poorest and most vulnerable people, good healthy practices in other areas of health where possible; improved dialogue between affected communities and health systems; improved stakeholders joint engagement between NGOs, Faith Based Organizations (FBOs), partners and the government; community  actors are consulted and enabled to act appropriately voices of affected people heard and Government and other actors respond to their needs and demands.</narrative>
  </description>
